AB  - The proceedings contain 84 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Artificial Intelligence. The topics include: Pre-training with Augmentations for Efficient Transfer in Model-Based Reinforcement Learning; dyPrune: Dynamic Pruning Rates for Neural Networks; robustness Analysis of Machine Learning Models Using Domain-Specific Test Data Perturbation; vocalization Features to Recognize Small Dolphin Species for Limited Datasets; covariance Kernel Learning Schemes for Gaussian Process Based Prediction Using Markov Chain Monte Carlo; a Review on Quadruped Manipulators; pollution Emission Patterns of Transportation in Porto, Portugal Through Network Analysis; analysis of Dam Natural Frequencies Using a Convolutional Neural Network; imbalanced Regression Evaluation Under Uncertain Domain Preferences; gamified CollectiveEyes: A Gamified Distributed Infrastructure for Collectively Sharing People’s Eyes; studying the Impact of Sampling in Highly Frequent Time Series; Mining Causal Links Between TV Sports Content and Real-World Data; hybrid SkipAwareRec: A Streaming Music Recommendation System; interpreting What is Important: An Explainability Approach and Study on Feature Selection; Time-Series Pattern Verification in CNC Machining Data; a Comparison of Automated Machine Learning Tools for Predicting Energy Building Consumption in Smart Cities; measuring Latency-Accuracy Trade-Offs in Convolutional Neural Networks; machine Learning Data Markets: Evaluating the Impact of Data Exchange on the Agent Learning Performance; multi-robot Adaptive Sampling for Supervised Spatiotemporal Forecasting; topic Model with Contextual Outlier Handling: a Study on Electronic Invoice Product Descriptions; Design and Development of Ontology for AI-Based Software Systems to Manage the Food Intake and Energy Consumption of Obesity, Diabetes and Tube Feeding Patients; tweet2Story: Extracting Narratives from Twitter; argumentation Mining from Textual Documents Combining Deep Learning